Hazel Keener https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hazel_Keener 0 Hazel Keener (October 22, 1904 – August 7, 1979) was a motion picture actress from Bettendorf, Iowa. She was raised in Davenport, Iowa. Keener won a national beauty contest sponsored by the Chicago Tribune and used her success to begin a film career in Hollywood. She was a lovely blonde, 5 feet 6 inches in height, 128 lbs., with a slender, athletic build. Her hair was chestnut brown and she had gray eyes.
